<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="141">
* 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:228190" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis (Myrma) schistacea st. atrociliata" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis (Myrma) schistacea st. atrociliata" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="schistacea" subGenus="Myrma" subSpecies="atrociliata">P. (Myrma) schistacea, st. atrociliata</taxonomicName>
, nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="141">
[[worker]]. - Noire, opaque, sculpture legerement plus forte que chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:193943" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis rugulosa Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis rugulosa Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugulosa">P. rugulosa Mayr</taxonomicName>
(luisante a un fort grossissement). Pubescence foncee. De nombreuses soies noires, epaisses et pointues, un peu obliques, sont dispersees sur tout le corps, les scapes et les pattes. (Chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:35075" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schistacea">P. schistacea</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:193943" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis rugulosa Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis rugulosa Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugulosa">P. rugulosa</taxonomicName>
les soies sont bien plus fines et blanchatres.) Forme de la tete comme chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:35075" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schistacea">P. schistacea</taxonomicName>
ou legerement plus large avec les yeux convexes. Epistome faiblement carene et echancre au milieu de son bord anterieur. Le scape depasse la tete de moins de la moitie de sa longueur (plus long et plus delie chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:35075" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schistacea">P. schistacea</taxonomicName>
). Pronotum plus large que long, le bord externe de l'epine se continue directement avec le bord du pronotum (fait un angle chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:35075" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schistacea">P. schistacea</taxonomicName>
). Mesono- tum et devant de la face basale de l'epinotum legerement coucave. Les dents de l'angle de l'epinotum tres petites. Ecaille comme chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:35075" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis schistacea (Gerstaecker)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schistacea">P. schistacea mais</taxonomicName>
les dents laterales plus reduites. Il differe de 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:193943" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Polyrhachis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyrhachis rugulosa Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Polyrhachis rugulosa Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugulosa">P. rugulosa</taxonomicName>
par sa pilosite tres abondante et noire.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="141">Uganda: Ibanda, dans la zone inferieure des monts Ruwenzori(ait. 1.400 m., 1909), 7 [[worker]].</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="141">Congo: Ubanghi; Benguela (variete a pilosite plus rare et plus courte, mais egalement noire, = var. Benguelensis, nov.).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
